 challenges, and inevitable conflicts—this book gives readers a greater understanding of the conservation ethic that emerged on the Great Plains as part of one of the most remarkable recovery efforts in the history of the Endangered Species Act.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBlack-footed ferretxConservationzUnited States. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aamerican conservation.  aanimals.  ablack footed ferret.  aconservation biology.  aconservation efforts.  aconservation ethics.  aconservation in the west.  acreatures.  aecological challenges.  aendangered species act.  aextinction.  afeared extinct.  aferrets.  agreat plains.  aintensive captive breeding.  anatural habitat.  anorth america.  anorth american wildlife.  apersonal account.  apolitical challenges.  ararest mammals.  arecovery efforts.  areintroduction into the wild.  asave the animals.  asocial challenges.  awildlife conservaton.  awildlife.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028165340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095816640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520958166423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520958166/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY